+- **🟠 Remove verbose `classifier_input` / `classifier_output` INFO logging from `exchange_classifier.py` before prod launch.** Story 6.9b smoke-gate 2026-05-22 added 2 `logger.info()` calls that emit the raw user transcription (`user_text`) + first 80 chars of `success_criteria` + first 80 chars of `last_character_line` + verdict + first 120 chars of raw classifier response on EVERY classify call. Kept INFO-level intentionally to help Story 6.10 (goal-based dialogue) debugging when it lands. **MUST be downgraded to DEBUG or removed before public launch** — `user_text` is raw STT output which is PII-equivalent (real users' practice utterances). Suggested action when Story 6.10 closes: either (a) downgrade both to `logger.debug()` for opt-in via `LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG`, or (b) delete entirely if Story 6.10 doesn't end up needing them. File: `server/pipeline/exchange_classifier.py` lines ~256-266 (`classifier_input` log) and ~328-330 (`classifier_output` log). Severity MEDIUM (privacy concern in prod, but no operational risk).
